#Text=Football : Manchester United push past Sheffield
#Text=Tuesday , April 17 , 2007
#Text=Manchester United 2 0 Sheffield United
#Text=Match Stats
#Text=Attendance 75,540
#Text=Goalscorers for Manchester United
#Text=Carrick ( 4 ' ) , Rooney ( 50 ' )
#Text=Goalscorers for Sheffield United
#Text=None Bookings ( Manchester United )
#Text=Smith , Rooney , Ronaldo ( Yellow ( 3 ) )
#Text=Bookings ( Sheffield United )
#Text=Geary , Morgan , Armstrong ( Yellow ( 3 ) )
#Text=Manchester United opened a temporary six-point lead over Chelsea on Tuesday with a 2-0 victory over Sheffield United .
#Text=The Blades are stuck in the relegation battle in the league , having only jumped out of the bottom three this past weeking after a 3-0 thumping of fellow strugglers West Ham .
#Text=The Red Devils on the other hand came into the game on a two game winning streak , having scored 11 goals in those two matches .
#Text=Man United started with the same striking pair used in the last two games in Wayne Rooney and Alan Smith .
#Text=Sheffield United boss Neil Warnock played Colin Kazim-Richards up front with Luton Shelton , who was earning his first start , on the attack .
#Text=The first chance of the match fell to the Yorkshire side as a free Kick by Tonge was driven low , but lacked the power to beat Reds keeper , Tomasz Kuszczak .
#Text=The Premiership leaders quickly made the Blades pay , and on 4 minutes , Michael Carrick received a pass from Cristiano Ronaldo , and chipped the ball over the sprawling Paddy Kenny .
#Text=Wayne Rooney then had a chance to double the Red Devils lead , but his shot lacked power and Kenny patted the ball away .
#Text=Another free kick was taken by Tonge for the Blades , and this one packed more power , but Kuszczak sprawled to make the stop .
#Text=Patrice Evra then had to be substituted for the Reds when he took a high challenge from Kazim-Richards , and was replaced by Keiron Richardson .
#Text=Smith was then forced to change his shorts after being caught by Matthew Kilgallon .
#Text=Luton Shelton continued to make an impact for Sheffield United as he blasted a shot just wide .
#Text=After the break , Rooney again had a chance to double United 's lead , but he was stopped by a well timed tackle from Chris Morgan .
#Text=Shelton meanwhile caused unrest in the Man United defence with strong runs , but no goals came of them .
#Text=Rooney finally scored his goal on 5 minutes when his run was met by Ryan Giggs ' pass , and the young Englishman blasted the ball far side on Kenny .
#Text=Shelton again threatened as he turned away from Wes Brown , but he then scooped the ball over the bar .
#Text=Danny Webber then had a chance for the Blades after beating out Heinze , but he raked his shot wide .
#Text=Kenny was then forced into action to make saves off both Ronaldo and Rooney , to keep the game at a respectable scoreline .
#Text=Shelton then had a legitimate claim for a penalty when he was brought down by Heinze in the area , but referee Rob Styles waved play on .
#Text=The decision all but ended the Blades hopes of a comeback , but they still continued to press as Tonge hit the post with a curling shot .
#Text=Kuszczak kept his clean sheat , however , and the Red Devils earned a valuable three points in the title race .
#Text=Manchester United 's next match will be another Premiership game against Middlesbrough at Old Trafford .
#Text=Sheffield United 's next , also in the Premiership , will be against main relegation rivals Charlton Athletic , and that match will be very important for both teams .
